  "text": "In the present study, several sequences were found in divisions with no cultured representatives. These include sequences from the OP10 group, first found in Obsidian Pool in Yellowstone National Park (21), the BD candidate division There is good support for the SPAM candidate division, which includes sequences from an arid Australian soil [CITATION_1] and from the Changjiang River [CITATION_2] , and SAM, together with sequences from an earthworm cast (17) and a polychlorinated biphenylcontaminated soil [CITATION_3] , may also prove to be a novel line of bacterial descent. The ecological role of these groups found in such diverse environments remains a mystery.",
